 about how the Grateful Dead Phenomenon was possible in the first place, what its social and aesthetic conditions of possibility were, and its results. This is the first book in a new series, Studies in the Grateful Dead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aImprovisation (Music)xSocial aspects. 0aRock musicxSocial aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 70(DE-601)1042794780(DE-588)4126830-1aSelbstorganisation2gnd 70(DE-601)1048058110(DE-588)4133965-4aAvantgarde2gnd 70(DE-601)1057206150(DE-588)4127993-1aImprovisation2gnd 70(DE-601)1058118150(DE-588)4115774-6aRockmusik2gnd 70(DE-601)1060914330(DE-588)4073840-1aKritische Theorie2gnd 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Rock.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961760423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520961760.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles